<div class="wikitext">
<a name="CommonAdjust"></a>
<h1>CommonAdjust</h1>
<p>
Define a chained item pricing scheme.
</p>
<a name="Synopsis"></a>
<h2>Synopsis</h2>
<p>
<!-- start of code block -->
<div class="code">
<table>
<tr>
<td class="code">
<span class="fixedwidth">
<span class="def_Syntax">CommonAdjust&nbsp; atom </span><span class="def_Symbol">[</span><span class="def_Symbol">;</span><span class="def_Syntax">atoms</span><span class="def_Symbol">.</span><span class="def_Symbol">.</span><span class="def_Symbol">.</span><span class="def_Symbol">]
</span></span>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>
<!-- end of code block -->
<a name="Scope"></a>
<h2>Scope</h2>
<p>
<!-- start of nosearch block -->
This directive is only available for use in the <em>local</em>
(<span class="fixedwidth">catalog.cfg</span>) configuration file.&nbsp;
It will not affect any other website in any way.&nbsp;
This directive will not work in the <em>global</em>
(<span class="fixedwidth">interchange.cfg</span>) configuration file.&nbsp;
<!-- end of nosearch block -->
<a name="Description"></a>
<h2>Description</h2>
<p>
This directive can be used to design a flexible, chained item pricing scheme.&nbsp;
The <span class="fixedwidth">CommonAdjust</span> <em>atoms</em> are chained price lookup and modification
instructions, which are explained on the
<a href="http://www.interchange-rtfm.pullingshots.ca/icdocs/Price_maintenance_with_CommonAdjust.html" title="Price maintenance with CommonAdjust">price maintenance with CommonAdjust</a>
page
</div>

